flowRoot.flowPara: PiTiVi will not ask you for licensing fees or lock you out of your data with "DRM", and will keep improving with each new release. And if you want to improve something in its behavior, you can.
Throw any format at it, as long as it is supported by the GStreamer Multimedia Framework, and PiTiVi will handle it.
A carefully-crafted user interface can suit both the newcomer and the professional.
Written in Python (a flexible, easy to learn high-level programming language), PiTiVi allows contributors to join the project with little barriers of entry.
A plugin system allows extending PiTiVi without needing to plunge at its core.
127 commits in the main development branch this month
We have some highly trained designer monkeys that can recite the GNOME Human Interface Guidelines in their sleep, backwards, all for you.
